60// The number of samples to extract for arithmetic intensity curves
61static const int ARITH_INTENSITY_CURVE_SAMPLE_N = 10;
62
63// Annotation position encoding
64enum class AnnotationPosType : int {
65 kPosNone = 0, // Does not have this kind of annotation
66 kPosInnerSpatial = 1, // The annotated iterator is the innermost spatial iterator
67 kPosMiddleSpatial = 2, // The annotated iterator is a middle spatial iterator
68 kPosOuterSpatial = 3, // The annotated iterator is the outermost spatial iterator
69 kPosInnerReduce = 4, // The annotated iterator is the innermost reduce iterator
70 kPosMiddleReduce = 5, // The annotated iterator is a middle reduce iterator
71 kPosOuterReduce = 6, // The annotated iterator is the outermost reduce iterator
72 kPosMixed = 7 // The annotated iterator is a mixed space and reduce iterator
73};
74
75// Buffer access type
76enum class BufferAccessType : int { kRead = 0, kWrite = 1, kReadWrite = 2, kUnknownRW = 3 };
77
78// Accesses to a buffer
79struct BufferAccess {
80 // data reuse type
81 BufferAccessType acc_type{BufferAccessType::kUnknownRW};
82 // Use a two-dimensional array to store multiple multi-dimensional accesses.
83 // The innermost vector stores the multi-dimensional indices of one access.
84 std::vector<std::vector<PrimExpr>> indices;
85};
86
87// Data reuse type
88enum class ReuseType : int { kLoopMultipleRead = 0, kSerialMultipleReadWrite = 1, kNoReuse = 2 };
89
90// Feature for an access of a buffer
91struct BufferAccessFeature {
92 std::string buffer_name; // The name of the buffer
93 BufferAccessType acc_type; // The type of the access
94 float bytes; // The touched memory in bytes
95 float unique_bytes; // The touched unique memory in bytes
96 float lines; // The number of touched cache lines
97 float unique_lines; // The number touched unique cache lines
98 ReuseType reuse_type; // Tye type of data reuse
99 float reuse_dis_iter; // The reuse distance in iterator number
100 float reuse_dis_bytes; // The reuse distance in total touched bytes
101 float reuse_ct; // The reuse ratio
102 float bytes_d_reuse_ct; // bytes / reuse_ct
103 float unique_bytes_d_reuse_ct; // unique_bytes / reuse_ct
104 float lines_d_reuse_ct; // lines / reuse_ct
105 float unique_lines_d_reuse_ct; // unique_lines / reuse_ct
106 float stride; // The stride in access
107};
108
109// Feature set of a BufferStore statement
110struct FeatureSet {
111 // Group 1: Computation related features
112 float float_mad; // The number of float MAD (Multiply–add) ops
113 float float_addsub; // The number of float add and sub ops
114 float float_mul; // The number of float multiply ops
115 float float_divmod; // The number of float div and mod ops
116 float float_cmp; // The number of float comparison ops
117 float float_math_func; // The number of float math func calls
118 float float_other_func; // The number of other float func calls
119 float int_mad; // The number of integer MAD (Multiply–add) ops
120 float int_addsub; // The number of integer add and sub ops
121 float int_mul; // The number of float multiply ops
122 float int_divmod; // The number of float div and mod ops
123 float int_cmp; // The number of float comparison ops
124 float int_math_func; // The number of float math func calls
125 float int_other_func; // The number of other float func calls
126 float bool_op; // The number of bool ops
127 float select_op; // The number of select ops
128 float vec_num; // The number of vectorized iterators
129 float vec_prod; // The product of the lengths of vectorized iterators
130 float vec_len; // The length of the innermost vectorized iterator
131 AnnotationPosType vec_type; // The type of vectorization position
132 float unroll_num; // The number of unrolled iterators
133 float unroll_prod; // The product of the lengths of vectorized iterators
134 float unroll_len; // The length of the innermost unrolled iterator
135 AnnotationPosType unroll_type; // The type of unroll position
136 float parallel_num; // The number of paralleled iterators
137 float parallel_prod; // The product of the lengths of paralleled iterators
138 float parallel_len; // The length of the innermost paralleled iterators
139 AnnotationPosType parallel_type; // The type of parallel position
140 float is_gpu; // Whether it is a GPU task
141 float blockIdx_x_len; // The length of blockIdx.x
142 float blockIdx_y_len; // The length of blockIdx.y
143 float blockIdx_z_len; // The length of blockIdx.z
144 float threadIdx_x_len; // The length of threadIdx.x
145 float threadIdx_y_len; // The length of threadIdx.y
146 float threadIdx_z_len; // The length of threadIdx.z
147 float vthread_len; // The length of virtual thread
148
149 // Group 2: Buffer access related features (per buffer)
150 std::vector<BufferAccessFeature> access_feas;
151
152 // Group 3: Arithmetic intensity related features
153 float arith_intensity_curve[ARITH_INTENSITY_CURVE_SAMPLE_N]; // points sampled from the
154 // arithmetic intensity curve
155
156 // Group 4: Allocation related features
157 float alloc_size; // The size of allocated buffer in bytes
158 float alloc_outer_prod; // The product of lengths of loops outside the scope of the allocation
159 float alloc_inner_prod; // The product of lengths of loops inside the score of the allocation
160 float alloc_prod; // alloc_outer_prod * alloc_inner_prod
161
162 // Group 5: Outer scope related features
163 float outer_prod; // The product of lengths of outer loops
164 float num_loops; // The number of outer loops
165 float auto_unroll_max_step; // The value of pragma "auto_unroll_max_step"
166};

168// Return whether a var is in an expr
169bool VarInExpr(const Var& var, const PrimExpr& expr) {
170 bool find = false;
171
172 PostOrderVisit(expr, [&find, &var](const ObjectRef& node) {
173 if (find) {
174 return;
175 }
176
177 if (const VarNode* op = node.as<VarNode>()) {
178 if (op == var.get()) {
179 find = true;
180 }
181 }
182 });
183
184 return find;
185}
186
187// Get position encoding for annotation
188AnnotationPosType GetAnnotationPosEncoding(const Var& var, const Array<PrimExpr>& spatial_args,
189 const Array<IterVar>& axis,
190 const Array<IterVar>& reduce_axis) {
191 // Try to match spatial args first
192 size_t find_i = 0;
193 size_t find_ct = 0;
194 for (size_t i = 0; i < spatial_args.size(); ++i) {
195 if (VarInExpr(var, spatial_args[i])) {
196 find_i = i;
197 find_ct += 1;
198 }
199 }
200
201 if (find_ct == 0) {
202 // If it is not found in spacial args, then it is a reduce iterator.
203 // Use name to match
204 const std::string& var_name = var->name_hint;
205 for (size_t i = 0; i < reduce_axis.size(); ++i) {
206 if (var_name.find(reduce_axis[i]->var->name_hint) != std::string::npos) {
207 find_i = i;
208 find_ct++;
209 }
210 }
211 if (find_ct >= 1) {
212 if (find_i == 0) {
213 return AnnotationPosType::kPosInnerReduce;
214 } else if (find_i == reduce_axis.size() - 1) {
215 return AnnotationPosType::kPosOuterReduce;
216 } else {
217 return AnnotationPosType::kPosMiddleReduce;
218 }
219 } else {
220 // If the axis is not found in both spatial args and reduce axis,
221 // then this stage must compute_at somewhere under this axis and this axis is simplified out
222 // We assume it is an outer spatial
223 return AnnotationPosType::kPosOuterSpatial;
224 }
225 } else if (find_ct == 1) {
226 if (find_i == spatial_args.size() - 1) {
227 return AnnotationPosType::kPosInnerSpatial;
228 } else if (find_i == 0) {
229 return AnnotationPosType::kPosOuterSpatial;
230 } else {
231 return AnnotationPosType::kPosMiddleSpatial;
232 }
233 } else {
234 return AnnotationPosType::kPosMixed;
235 }
236}
237
238// Return the maximum extent of a for loop
239int64_t GetLoopExtent(const ForNode* node, const Analyzer& ana) {
240 int64_t bound = ana.const_int_bound(node->extent)->max_value;
241 if (bound == ConstIntBound::kPosInf) {
242 return 1; // Analyzer could not determine a valid bound, use 1 instead.
243 } else {
244 return bound;
245 }
246}

248// Count math ops in an expr
249class MathOpCounter : public StmtExprVisitor {
250 public:
251#define VisitBinary(Type, float_ct, int_ct) \
252 void VisitExpr_(const Type* op) final { \
253 if (op->a.dtype().is_float() || op->a.dtype().is_bfloat16()) { \
254 float_ct += op->a.dtype().lanes(); \
255 } else { \
256 int_ct += op->a.dtype().lanes(); \
257 } \
258 StmtExprVisitor::VisitExpr_(op); \
259 }
260
261 VisitBinary(AddNode, float_addsub, int_addsub);
262 VisitBinary(SubNode, float_addsub, int_addsub);
263 VisitBinary(MulNode, float_mul, int_mul);
264 VisitBinary(DivNode, float_divmod, int_divmod);
265 VisitBinary(ModNode, float_divmod, int_divmod);
266 VisitBinary(FloorDivNode, float_divmod, int_divmod);
267 VisitBinary(FloorModNode, float_divmod, int_divmod);
268 VisitBinary(MaxNode, float_cmp, int_cmp);
269 VisitBinary(MinNode, float_cmp, int_cmp);
270 VisitBinary(EQNode, float_cmp, int_cmp);
271 VisitBinary(NENode, float_cmp, int_cmp);
272 VisitBinary(LTNode, float_cmp, int_cmp);
273 VisitBinary(LENode, float_cmp, int_cmp);
274 VisitBinary(GTNode, float_cmp, int_cmp);
275 VisitBinary(GENode, float_cmp, int_cmp);
276
277#undef VisitBinary
278
279 void VisitExpr_(const AndNode* op) final {
280 bool_op++;
281 StmtExprVisitor::VisitExpr_(op);
282 }
283 void VisitExpr_(const OrNode* op) final {
284 bool_op++;
285 StmtExprVisitor::VisitExpr_(op);
286 }
287 void VisitExpr_(const NotNode* op) final {
288 bool_op++;
289 StmtExprVisitor::VisitExpr_(op);
290 }
291 void VisitExpr_(const SelectNode* op) final {
292 select_op++;
293 StmtExprVisitor::VisitExpr_(op);
294 }
295
296 void VisitExpr_(const CallNode* op) final {
297 auto* pop = op->op.as<OpNode>();
298 ICHECK(pop != nullptr);
299 auto effect_kind = op_call_effect_[GetRef<Op>(pop)];
300 bool is_pure =
301 effect_kind == CallEffectKind::kPure || effect_kind == CallEffectKind::kExprAnnotation;
302
303 if (is_pure) {
304 if (op->dtype.is_float() || op->dtype.is_bfloat16()) {
305 float_math_func++;
306 } else {
307 int_math_func++;
308 }
309 } else {
310 if (op->dtype.is_float() || op->dtype.is_bfloat16()) {
311 float_other_func++;
312 } else {
313 int_other_func++;
314 }
315 }
316 StmtExprVisitor::VisitExpr_(op);
317 }
318
319 // todo(merrymercy): Detect MAD (Multiply–add)
320 size_t float_mad{0}; // The number of float MAD (Multiply–add) ops
321 size_t float_addsub{0}; // The number of float add and sub ops
322 size_t float_mul{0}; // The number of float multiply ops
323 size_t float_divmod{0}; // The number of float div and mod ops
324 size_t float_cmp{0}; // The number of float comparison ops
325 size_t float_math_func{0}; // The number of float math func calls
326 size_t float_other_func{0}; // The number of other float func calls
327 size_t int_mad{0}; // The number of integer MAD (Multiply–add) ops
328 size_t int_addsub{0}; // The number of integer add and sub ops
329 size_t int_mul{0}; // The number of float multiply ops
330 size_t int_divmod{0}; // The number of float div and mod ops
331 size_t int_cmp{0}; // The number of float comparison ops
332 size_t int_math_func{0}; // The number of float math func calls
333 size_t int_other_func{0}; // The number of other float func calls
334 size_t bool_op{0}; // The number of bool ops
335 size_t select_op{0}; // The number of select ops
336
337 OpAttrMap<TCallEffectKind> op_call_effect_ = Op::GetAttrMap<TCallEffectKind>("TCallEffectKind");
338};

340// Extract all buffer accesses in an expr
341class BufferAccessExtractor : public StmtExprVisitor {
342 public:
343 void ExtractReads(const PrimExpr& expr) { this->VisitExpr(expr); }
344
345 void InsertAccess(const Var& buf, BufferAccessType acc_type, const Array<PrimExpr>& indices) {
346 BufferAccess& acc = buf_accesses[buf];
347 acc.acc_type = acc_type;
348 acc.indices.push_back(std::vector<PrimExpr>(indices.begin(), indices.end()));
349 }
350
351 void VisitExpr_(const BufferLoadNode* op) final {
352 AddAccess(op->buffer->data, op->indices);
353 StmtExprVisitor::VisitExpr_(op);
354 }
355
356 void AddAccess(const Var& buffer, const Array<PrimExpr>& indices) {
357 BufferAccess& acc = buf_accesses[buffer];
358 switch (acc.acc_type) {
359 case BufferAccessType::kRead:
360 break;
361 case BufferAccessType::kWrite:
362 acc.acc_type = BufferAccessType::kReadWrite;
363 break;
364 case BufferAccessType::kReadWrite:
365 break;
366 case BufferAccessType::kUnknownRW:
367 default:
368 acc.acc_type = BufferAccessType::kRead;
369 break;
370 }
371
372 if (acc.acc_type != BufferAccessType::kReadWrite) {
373 // If a buffer is both read and written, in the tvm DSL, it must be a update,
374 // so the indices should be the same. Then we can skip appending indices for it.
375 // Otherwise we do the following.
376 buf_accesses[buffer].indices.push_back(std::vector<PrimExpr>(indices.begin(), indices.end()));
377 }
378 }
379
380 BufferMap<BufferAccess> buf_accesses;
381};

383// Compute the coefficient for an loop iterator in an expression
384// Note: we use an approximation strategy to find coefficient.
385// Hopefully, it is faster than DetectLinearEquation and can handle more cases (non-linear)
386class CoefficientExtractor : public StmtExprVisitor {
387 public:
388 void VisitExpr_(const MulNode* node) final {
389 StmtExprVisitor::VisitExpr_(node);
390 if (visited_var) {
391 if (!visited_add) {
392 if (auto a = node->a.as<IntImmNode>()) {
393 visited_mul = true;
394 stride = a->value;
395 } else if (auto b = node->b.as<IntImmNode>()) {
396 visited_mul = true;
397 stride = b->value;
398 }
399 }
400 }
401 }
402
403 void VisitExpr_(const AddNode* node) final {
404 StmtExprVisitor::VisitExpr_(node);
405 if (visited_var) {
406 if (!visited_mul) {
407 visited_add = true;
408 stride = 1;
409 }
410 }
411 }
412
413 void VisitExpr_(const VarNode* node) final {
414 if (node == var_) {
415 visited_var = true;
416 // This is a magic default stride in case our approximation strategy fails
417 stride = 2;
418 }
419 }
420
421 int ExtractCoefficient(const PrimExpr& expr, const VarNode* var) {
422 visited_var = visited_mul = visited_add = false;
423 var_ = var;
424
425 this->VisitExpr(expr);
426
427 if (visited_var && !visited_mul && !visited_add) {
428 return 1;
429 } else {
430 return stride;
431 }
432 }
433
434 bool visited_var{false};
435 bool visited_mul{false};
436 bool visited_add{false};
437 int stride{0};
438
439 private:
440 const VarNode* var_{nullptr};
441};
442
443// Compute stride for the accesses to a buffer
444int64_t ComputeStride(const std::vector<std::vector<PrimExpr>>& indices,
445 const std::vector<int>& shape, const VarNode* stride_var) {
446 int64_t min_stride = std::numeric_limits<int64_t>::max();
447 bool find = false;
448 CoefficientExtractor extractor;
449
450 for (const auto& index : indices) {
451 int64_t shape_stride = 1;
452 for (int i = static_cast<int>(index.size()) - 1; i >= 0; i--) {
453 int coefficient = extractor.ExtractCoefficient(index[i], stride_var);
454 if (extractor.visited_var) {
455 find = true;
456 min_stride = std::min(min_stride, std::abs(coefficient) * shape_stride);
457 break;
458 }
459 shape_stride *= shape[i];
460 }
461 }
462
463 return find ? min_stride : 0;
464}

466// Compute touched bytes and cache lines for accesses to a buffer
467void ComputeRegion(const std::vector<std::vector<PrimExpr>>& indices, arith::Analyzer* ana,
468 std::vector<int>* region) {
469 region->clear();
470
471 if (indices.empty()) {
472 return;
473 }
474
475 region->reserve(indices[0].size());
476
477 if (indices.size() == 1) {
478 for (const auto& index : indices[0]) {
479 ConstIntBound bound = ana->const_int_bound(index);
480 region->push_back(bound->max_value - bound->min_value + 1);
481 }
482 } else {
483 // future(lmzheng): implement a more accurate IntSet?
484 for (size_t i = 0; i < indices[0].size(); ++i) {
485 int64_t minimum = ConstIntBound::kPosInf, maximum = ConstIntBound::kNegInf;
486 for (size_t j = 0; j < indices.size(); ++j) {
487 ConstIntBound bound = ana->const_int_bound(indices[j][i]);
488
489 minimum = std::min(minimum, bound->min_value);
490 maximum = std::max(maximum, bound->max_value);
491 }
492 region->push_back(maximum - minimum + 1);
493 }
494 }
495}

497// Compute reuse distance and reuse ratio for accesses to a buffer
498// return values: reuse_type, reuse_dis_iter, reuse_dis_bytes, reuse_ct
499std::tuple<ReuseType, float, float, float> ComputeReuse(
500 const Var& buf, const std::vector<std::vector<PrimExpr>>& indices,
501 const std::vector<const ForNode*>& for_loop_stack,
502 const std::unordered_map<const ForNode*,
503 BufferMap<std::vector<std::tuple<BufferAccessType, int64_t, int>>>>&
504 for_touch_regions,
505 const Analyzer& ana) {
506 float reuse_dis_iter = 1.0f;
507 float reuse_dis_bytes = -1.0f;
508
509 for (int i = static_cast<int>(for_loop_stack.size()) - 1; i >= 0; --i) {
510 const ForNode* cur_for = for_loop_stack[i];
511 bool find = false;
512
513 for (size_t j = 0; j < indices.size(); j++) {
514 for (size_t k = 0; k < indices[j].size(); k++) {
515 if (VarInExpr(cur_for->loop_var, indices[j][k])) {
516 find = true;
517 break;
518 }
519 }
520 if (find) {
521 break;
522 }
523 }
524
525 int64_t extent = GetLoopExtent(for_loop_stack[i], ana);
526 if (find) {
527 // accumulate/update reuse distance
528 reuse_dis_iter *= extent;
529 reuse_dis_bytes = 0.0f;
530 for (const auto& iter : for_touch_regions.at(cur_for)) {
531 for (const auto& access : iter.second) {
532 reuse_dis_bytes += std::get<1>(access) * std::get<2>(access);
533 }
534 }
535 } else {
536 // Have LoopMultipleRead reuse
537 if (reuse_dis_bytes < 0) {
538 // For the reuse in the innermost axis, the above code won't be executed.
539 // So we compute bytes here
540 reuse_dis_bytes = 0.0f;
541 for (const auto& iter : for_touch_regions.at(cur_for)) {
542 for (const auto& access : iter.second) {
543 reuse_dis_bytes += 1 * std::get<2>(access);
544 }
545 }
546 }
547 return std::make_tuple(ReuseType::kLoopMultipleRead, reuse_dis_iter, reuse_dis_bytes, extent);
548 }
549
550 const BufferMap<std::vector<std::tuple<BufferAccessType, int64_t, int>>>& buffer_map =
551 for_touch_regions.at(cur_for);
552
553 int serial_reuse = static_cast<int>(buffer_map.at(buf).size()) - 1;
554 if (serial_reuse > 0) {
555 int64_t extent = GetLoopExtent(cur_for, ana);
556
557 // Have SerialMultipleReadWrite reuse
558 reuse_dis_iter = std::numeric_limits<float>::max();
559 for (const auto& acc_info : buffer_map.at(buf)) {
560 reuse_dis_iter = std::min(reuse_dis_iter, static_cast<float>(std::get<1>(acc_info)));
561 }
562
563 reuse_dis_bytes = 0.0f;
564 for (const auto& iter : for_touch_regions.at(cur_for)) {
565 for (const auto& access : iter.second) {
566 reuse_dis_bytes += std::get<1>(access) * std::get<2>(access);
567 }
568 }
569
570 return std::make_tuple(ReuseType::kSerialMultipleReadWrite, reuse_dis_iter / extent,
571 reuse_dis_bytes / extent, serial_reuse);
572 }
573 }
574
575 return std::make_tuple(ReuseType::kNoReuse, 0, 0, 0);
576}

578// Extract features for every BufferStore statement
579//
580// This visitor assumes that loop bounds do no depend on data or on parent loop
581// bounds. For example, `for i in .. { for j in range(i, ..) }` would result in
582// inaccurate features. This visitor also does not take conditionals into
583// consideration when creating features. Each branch of the conditional is
584// taken at the same time.
585class PerStoreFeatureExtractor : public StmtExprVisitor {
586 public:
587 explicit PerStoreFeatureExtractor(int cache_line_size, const Map<Var, Buffer>& existing_buffers)
588 : cache_line_size_(cache_line_size) {
589 for (const auto& buffer : existing_buffers) {
590 buffer_shapes[buffer.first] = buffer.second->shape;
591 buffer_dtypes[buffer.first] = buffer.second->dtype;
592 // Also need to add a reference from the buffers internal variable. This
593 // is usually how buffers are referenced within the body of a PrimFunc
594 buffer_shapes[buffer.second->data] = buffer.second->shape;
595 buffer_dtypes[buffer.second->data] = buffer.second->dtype;
596 }
597 }
598
599 void VisitStmt_(const AttrStmtNode* node) final {
600 if (node->attr_key == tir::attr::thread_extent || node->attr_key == tir::attr::virtual_thread) {
601 const Var& var = node->node.as<IterVarNode>()->var;
602 int extent = GetIntImm(node->value);
603
604 int* plen = nullptr;
605
606 const std::string& name = var.get()->name_hint;
607 if (node->attr_key == tir::attr::thread_extent) {
608 if (name == "blockIdx.x") {
609 plen = &blockIdx_x_len_;
610 } else if (name == "blockIdx.y") {
611 plen = &block_idx_y_len_;
612 } else if (name == "blockIdx.z") {
613 plen = &block_idx_z_len_;
614 } else if (name == "threadIdx.x") {
615 plen = &threadIdx_x_len_;
616 } else if (name == "threadIdx.y") {
617 plen = &thread_idx_y_len_;
618 } else if (name == "threadIdx.z") {
619 plen = &thread_idx_z_len_;
620 } else {
621 LOG(FATAL) << "invalid thread itervar " + name;
622 }
623 } else {
624 plen = &vthread_len_;
625 }
626
627 int extent_before = *plen;
628 if (node->attr_key == tir::attr::thread_extent) {
629 *plen = extent;
630 } else {
631 *plen *= extent;
632 }
633
634 is_gpu_ = true;
635
636 // make a fake for node for blockIdx.x or threadIdx.x
637 Stmt fake_for_node = For(var, 0, extent, ForKind::kParallel, node->body);
638
639 outer_loop_prod_ *= extent;
640 for_loop_stack_.push_back(fake_for_node.as<ForNode>());
641 variable_definition_stack_.push_back({});
642 StmtExprVisitor::VisitStmt_(node);
643 variable_definition_stack_.pop_back();
644 for_loop_stack_.pop_back();
645 outer_loop_prod_ /= extent;
646
647 *plen = extent_before;
648 } else if (node->attr_key == "pragma_auto_unroll_max_step") {
649 int value = GetIntImm(node->value);
650
651 int16_t old_value = cur_auto_unroll_max_step_;
652 cur_auto_unroll_max_step_ = value;
653 StmtExprVisitor::VisitStmt_(node);
654 cur_auto_unroll_max_step_ = old_value;
655 } else {
656 StmtExprVisitor::VisitStmt_(node);
657 }
658 }
659
660 void VisitStmt_(const ForNode* node) final {
661 ana_.Bind(node->loop_var, Range::FromMinExtent(node->min, node->extent));
662 int64_t loop_extent = GetLoopExtent(node, ana_);
663
664 if (node->kind == ForKind::kVectorized) {
665 vec_for_stack_.push_back(node);
666 } else if (node->kind == ForKind::kUnrolled) {
667 unroll_for_stack_.push_back(node);
668 } else if (node->kind == ForKind::kParallel) {
669 parallel_for_stack_.push_back(node);
670 }
671
672 outer_loop_prod_ *= loop_extent;
673 for_loop_stack_.push_back(node);
674 variable_definition_stack_.push_back({});
675 StmtExprVisitor::VisitStmt_(node);
676 variable_definition_stack_.pop_back();
677 for_loop_stack_.pop_back();
678 outer_loop_prod_ /= loop_extent;
679
680 if (node->kind == ForKind::kVectorized) {
681 vec_for_stack_.pop_back();
682 } else if (node->kind == ForKind::kUnrolled) {
683 unroll_for_stack_.pop_back();
684 } else if (node->kind == ForKind::kParallel) {
685 parallel_for_stack_.pop_back();
686 }
687 }

689 void VisitExpr_(const BufferLoadNode* node) final {
690 // Store buffer shape/dtype. It may already be stored.
691 buffer_shapes[node->buffer->data] = node->buffer->shape;
692 buffer_dtypes[node->buffer->data] = node->buffer->dtype;
693 StmtExprVisitor::VisitExpr_(node);
694 }
695
696 void VisitStmt_(const BufferStoreNode* node) final {
697 // Store buffer shape/dtype. It may already be stored.
698 buffer_shapes[node->buffer->data] = node->buffer->shape;
699 buffer_dtypes[node->buffer->data] = node->buffer->dtype;
700
701 MathOpCounter math_op_counter;
702 math_op_counter(node->value);
703 std::vector<float> mem_bytes_list;
704 std::vector<float> compute_ops_list;
705 double cur_compute_ops;
706
707 // Group 1: Computation related features
708 ExtractComputationFeature(node->buffer->data, node->indices, math_op_counter);
709
710 // Group 2: Buffer access related features (per buffer)
711 ExtractBufferAccessFeature(node->buffer->data, node->indices, node->value, math_op_counter,
712 &cur_compute_ops, &compute_ops_list, &mem_bytes_list);
713
714 // Group 3: Arithmetic intensity related features
715 ExtractArithmeticIntensityFeature(node->buffer->data, cur_compute_ops, compute_ops_list,
716 mem_bytes_list);
717
718 // Group 4: Allocation related features
719 ExtractOuterScopeFeature(node->buffer->data);
720 }

724 buffer_shapes[node->buffer->data] = node->buffer->shape;
725 buffer_dtypes[node->buffer->data] = node->buffer->dtype;
726 StmtExprVisitor::VisitStmt_(node);
727
728 // Group 5: Outer scope related features
729 ExtractAllocationFeature(node);
730 }

739 }

747 StmtExprVisitor::VisitStmt_(node);

750 // Extract computation related features (group 1)
751 void ExtractComputationFeature(const Var& buffer, const Array<PrimExpr>& indices,
752 const MathOpCounter& math_op_counter) {
753 FeatureSet& fea = buffer_features[buffer];
754
755 // Computation related features
756 fea.float_mad += outer_loop_prod_ * math_op_counter.float_mad;
757 fea.float_addsub += outer_loop_prod_ * math_op_counter.float_addsub;
758 fea.float_mul += outer_loop_prod_ * math_op_counter.float_mul;
759 fea.float_divmod += outer_loop_prod_ * math_op_counter.float_divmod;
760 fea.float_cmp += outer_loop_prod_ * math_op_counter.float_cmp;
761 fea.float_math_func += outer_loop_prod_ * math_op_counter.float_math_func;
762 fea.float_other_func += outer_loop_prod_ * math_op_counter.float_other_func;
763 fea.int_mad += outer_loop_prod_ * math_op_counter.int_mad;
764 fea.int_addsub += outer_loop_prod_ * math_op_counter.int_addsub;
765 fea.int_mul += outer_loop_prod_ * math_op_counter.int_mul;
766 fea.int_divmod += outer_loop_prod_ * math_op_counter.int_divmod;
767 fea.int_math_func += outer_loop_prod_ * math_op_counter.int_math_func;
768 fea.int_cmp += outer_loop_prod_ * math_op_counter.int_cmp;
769 fea.int_other_func += outer_loop_prod_ * math_op_counter.int_other_func;
770 fea.bool_op += outer_loop_prod_ * math_op_counter.bool_op;
771 fea.select_op += outer_loop_prod_ * math_op_counter.select_op;
772
773 fea.vec_len = fea.unroll_len = fea.parallel_len = 0.0f;
774 fea.vec_type = fea.unroll_type = fea.parallel_type = AnnotationPosType::kPosNone;
775
776 fea.vec_num = vec_for_stack_.size();
777 if (!vec_for_stack_.empty()) {
778 fea.vec_len = GetLoopExtent(vec_for_stack_.back(), ana_);
779 fea.vec_prod = 1.0;
780 for (const ForNode* pfor : vec_for_stack_) {
781 fea.vec_prod *= GetLoopExtent(pfor, ana_);
782 }
783 fea.vec_type = AnnotationPosType::kPosMixed;
784 // todo(merrymercy): this feature requires operation (tvm.compute) information
785 // GetAnnotationPosEncoding(vec_for_stack_.back()->loop_var,
786 // node->args, pcompute->axis, pcompute->reduce_axis);
787 }
788
789 fea.unroll_num = unroll_for_stack_.size();
790 if (!unroll_for_stack_.empty()) {
791 fea.unroll_len = GetLoopExtent(unroll_for_stack_.back(), ana_);
792 fea.unroll_prod = 1.0;
793 for (const ForNode* pfor : unroll_for_stack_) {
794 fea.unroll_prod *= GetLoopExtent(pfor, ana_);
795 }
796 fea.unroll_type = AnnotationPosType::kPosMixed;
797 // GetAnnotationPosEncoding(unroll_for_stack_.back()->loop_var,
798 // node->args, pcompute->axis, pcompute->reduce_axis);
799 }
800
801 fea.parallel_num = parallel_for_stack_.size();
802 if (!parallel_for_stack_.empty()) {
803 fea.parallel_len = GetLoopExtent(parallel_for_stack_.back(), ana_);
804 fea.parallel_prod = 1.0;
805 for (const ForNode* pfor : parallel_for_stack_) {
806 fea.parallel_prod *= GetLoopExtent(pfor, ana_);
807 }
808 fea.parallel_type = AnnotationPosType::kPosMixed;
809 // GetAnnotationPosEncoding(parallel_for_stack_.back()->loop_var,
810 // node->args, pcompute->axis, pcompute->reduce_axis);
811 }
812
813 // GPU threads
814 fea.is_gpu = is_gpu_;
815 fea.blockIdx_x_len = blockIdx_x_len_;
816 fea.blockIdx_y_len = block_idx_y_len_;
817 fea.blockIdx_z_len = block_idx_z_len_;
818 fea.threadIdx_x_len = threadIdx_x_len_;
819 fea.threadIdx_y_len = thread_idx_y_len_;
820 fea.threadIdx_z_len = thread_idx_z_len_;
821 fea.vthread_len = vthread_len_;
822 }

824 // Extract buffer access related features (group 2)
825 void ExtractBufferAccessFeature(const Var& buffer, const Array<PrimExpr>& indices,
826 const PrimExpr& value, const MathOpCounter& math_op_counter,
827 double* cur_compute_ops, std::vector<float>* compute_ops_list,
828 std::vector<float>* mem_bytes_list) {
829 FeatureSet& fea = buffer_features[buffer];
830
831 // Extract all buffer accesses
832 std::vector<BufferAccessFeature> acc_feas;
833 BufferAccessExtractor buf_extractor;
834 buf_extractor.InsertAccess(buffer, BufferAccessType::kWrite, indices);
835 buf_extractor.ExtractReads(value);
836
837 mem_bytes_list->reserve(for_loop_stack_.size());
838 compute_ops_list->reserve(for_loop_stack_.size());
839
840 *cur_compute_ops = math_op_counter.float_mad + math_op_counter.float_addsub +
841 math_op_counter.float_mul + math_op_counter.float_divmod +
842 math_op_counter.float_cmp + math_op_counter.float_math_func +
843 math_op_counter.float_other_func;
844
845 ICHECK_EQ(for_loop_stack_.size(), variable_definition_stack_.size())
846 << "variable_definition_stack_ should mirror for_loop_stack_ in size";
847 std::vector<int> tmp_region;
848 for (int i = static_cast<int>(for_loop_stack_.size()) - 1; i >= 0; i--) {
849 const ForNode* p_for = for_loop_stack_[i];
850
851 // Construct a local analyzer context which contains definitions (for and
852 // let) from innermost loops up to and including `i`. For loop variable
853 // definitions in loops more outer than `i` are set to 1 so that we can
854 // get per-loop-iteration features. Note that we add these definitions
855 // from outermost to innermost because inner definitions may depend on
856 // outer ones.
857 Analyzer local_analyzer;
858 for (int j = 0; j < i; j++) {
859 local_analyzer.Bind(for_loop_stack_.at(j)->loop_var,
860 Range::FromMinExtent(for_loop_stack_.at(j)->min, 1));
861 }
862 for (int j = i; j < static_cast<int>(for_loop_stack_.size()); j++) {
863 local_analyzer.Bind(
864 for_loop_stack_.at(j)->loop_var,
865 Range::FromMinExtent(for_loop_stack_.at(j)->min, for_loop_stack_.at(j)->extent));
866 for (auto definition : variable_definition_stack_.at(j)) {
867 local_analyzer.Bind(std::get<0>(definition), std::get<1>(definition));
868 }
869 }
870
871 // Note, here we do overwrite.
872 // So if there are multiple BufferStoreNode, the last one will overwrite the first few.
873 // e.g. The update part in gemm will overwrite the init part.
874 BufferMap<std::vector<std::tuple<BufferAccessType, int64_t, int>>>& buffer_regions_map =
875 for_touch_regions_[p_for];
876
877 int64_t mem_bytes = 0;
878 for (const auto& x : buf_extractor.buf_accesses) {
879 const Var& t = x.first;
880 const BufferAccess& acc = x.second;
881
882 ComputeRegion(acc.indices, &local_analyzer, &tmp_region);
883 int64_t touched_size = ElementProduct(tmp_region);
884 touched_size = std::max<int64_t>(0, touched_size);
885 buffer_regions_map[t].push_back(
886 std::make_tuple(acc.acc_type, touched_size, buffer_dtypes.at(t).bytes()));
887 mem_bytes += touched_size * buffer_dtypes.at(t).bytes();
888 }
889
890 mem_bytes_list->push_back(mem_bytes);
891 *cur_compute_ops *= GetLoopExtent(for_loop_stack_[i], local_analyzer);
892 compute_ops_list->push_back(*cur_compute_ops);
893 }
894
895 // Buffer access related features (per buffer)
896 for (const auto& x : buf_extractor.buf_accesses) {
897 const Var& t = x.first;
898 const BufferAccess& acc = x.second;
899
900 std::vector<int> int_shape;
901 for (const auto& dim : buffer_shapes.at(t)) {
902 int_shape.push_back(GetIntImm(dim));
903 }
904
905 size_t ele_bytes = buffer_dtypes.at(t).bytes();
906
907 // calculate bytes
908 float bytes = outer_loop_prod_ * ele_bytes;
909 float unique_bytes;
910
911 // calculate cache lines
912 int64_t stride;
913 float lines;
914 float unique_lines;
915
916 if (for_loop_stack_.empty()) {
917 unique_bytes = ele_bytes;
918 stride = 0;
919 lines = 1.0f;
920 unique_lines = 1.0f;
921 } else {
922 unique_bytes = static_cast<float>(
923 std::get<1>(for_touch_regions_[for_loop_stack_.front()][t].front())) *
924 ele_bytes;
925
926 stride = 0;
927 int64_t reduce_ratio = 1;
928
929 int i;
930 for (i = static_cast<int>(for_loop_stack_.size()) - 1; i >= 0; i--) {
931 stride = ComputeStride(acc.indices, int_shape, for_loop_stack_[i]->loop_var.get());
932 if (stride != 0) {
933 break;
934 }
935 reduce_ratio *= GetLoopExtent(for_loop_stack_.back(), ana_);
936 }
937
938 lines = outer_loop_prod_ / reduce_ratio *
939 std::min(1.0f, 1.0f * stride * ele_bytes / cache_line_size_);
940 lines = std::max(lines, 1.0f);
941
942 // convert `stride` back to the stride of the innermost iterator
943 stride = (i == static_cast<int>(for_loop_stack_.size()) - 1 ? stride : 0);
944
945 float n_continuous = ele_bytes;
946 for (int i = std::min(static_cast<int>(tmp_region.size()) - 1,
947 static_cast<int>(int_shape.size()) - 1);
948 i >= 0; i--) {
949 if (tmp_region[i] == int_shape[i]) {
950 n_continuous *= tmp_region[i];
951 break;
952 }
953 }
954 unique_lines = unique_bytes / std::min(n_continuous, static_cast<float>(cache_line_size_));
955 unique_lines = std::max(unique_lines, 1.0f);
956 }
957
958 auto [reuse_type, reuse_dis_iter, reuse_dis_bytes, reuse_ct] =
959 ComputeReuse(t, acc.indices, for_loop_stack_, for_touch_regions_, ana_);
960
961 acc_feas.emplace_back();
962 BufferAccessFeature& acc_fea = acc_feas.back();
963
964 // TODO(tkonolige): save buffer names and use those instead?
965 acc_fea.buffer_name = t->name_hint;
966 acc_fea.acc_type = acc.acc_type;
967 acc_fea.stride = stride;
968 acc_fea.bytes = bytes;
969 acc_fea.unique_bytes = unique_bytes;
970 acc_fea.lines = lines;
971 acc_fea.unique_lines = unique_lines;
972 acc_fea.reuse_type = reuse_type;
973 acc_fea.reuse_dis_iter = reuse_dis_iter;
974 acc_fea.reuse_dis_bytes = reuse_dis_bytes;
975 acc_fea.reuse_ct = reuse_ct;
976 if (acc_fea.reuse_ct > 0.5) {
977 acc_fea.bytes_d_reuse_ct = bytes / reuse_ct;
978 acc_fea.unique_bytes_d_reuse_ct = unique_bytes / reuse_ct;
979 acc_fea.lines_d_reuse_ct = lines / reuse_ct;
980 acc_fea.unique_lines_d_reuse_ct = unique_lines / reuse_ct;
981 } else {
982 // no reuse, multiply by a magic number '2'
983 acc_fea.bytes_d_reuse_ct = bytes * 2;
984 acc_fea.unique_bytes_d_reuse_ct = unique_bytes * 2;
985 acc_fea.lines_d_reuse_ct = lines * 2;
986 acc_fea.unique_lines_d_reuse_ct = unique_lines * 2;
987 }
988 }
989
990 fea.access_feas = acc_feas;
991 }
992
993 // Extract arithmetic intensity related feature (group 3)
994 void ExtractArithmeticIntensityFeature(const Var& buffer, double cur_compute_ops,
995 const std::vector<float>& compute_ops_list,
996 const std::vector<float>& mem_bytes_list) {
997 FeatureSet& fea = buffer_features[buffer];
998
999 // Compute arithmetic intensity curve (y axis : arithmetic intensity, x axis : flops).
1000 // We use piecewise linear interpolation to fit this curve.
1001 int pt = 0;
1002 if (cur_compute_ops <= 0 || compute_ops_list.empty()) {
1003 std::fill(fea.arith_intensity_curve,
1004 fea.arith_intensity_curve + ARITH_INTENSITY_CURVE_SAMPLE_N, 0.0);
1005 } else {
1006 for (size_t i = 0; i < ARITH_INTENSITY_CURVE_SAMPLE_N; ++i) {
1007 float cur_compute_ops = compute_ops_list.back() * (i + 1) / ARITH_INTENSITY_CURVE_SAMPLE_N;
1008 while (compute_ops_list[pt] < cur_compute_ops - 1e-4) {
1009 pt++;
1010 }
1011 ICHECK_LT(pt, compute_ops_list.size());
1012
1013 float value;
1014 if (pt == 0) {
1015 value = compute_ops_list[pt] / mem_bytes_list[pt];
1016 } else {
1017 float base = compute_ops_list[pt - 1] / mem_bytes_list[pt - 1];
1018 float slope = (compute_ops_list[pt] / mem_bytes_list[pt] -
1019 compute_ops_list[pt - 1] / mem_bytes_list[pt - 1]) /
1020 (compute_ops_list[pt] - compute_ops_list[pt - 1]);
1021 value = base + slope * (cur_compute_ops - compute_ops_list[pt - 1]);
1022 }
1023 fea.arith_intensity_curve[i] = value;
1024 }
1025 }
1026 }

1028 // Extract allocation related features (group 4)
1029 void ExtractAllocationFeature(const BufferRealizeNode* node) {
1030 FeatureSet& fea = buffer_features[node->buffer->data];
1031
1032 float allocation_size = 1.0f;
1033 for (const auto& x : node->bounds) {
1034 allocation_size *= GetIntImm(x->extent);
1035 }
1036 // allocation feature
1037 fea.alloc_size = allocation_size * node->buffer->dtype.bytes();
1038 fea.alloc_prod = allocation_size * outer_loop_prod_;
1039 fea.alloc_outer_prod = outer_loop_prod_;
1040 fea.alloc_inner_prod = fea.outer_prod / outer_loop_prod_;
1041 }
1042
1043 void ExtractAllocationFeature(const AllocateNode* node) {
1044 FeatureSet& fea = buffer_features[node->buffer_var];
1045
1046 float allocation_size = 1.0f;
1047 for (const auto& x : node->extents) {
1048 // TODO(tkonolige): will not handle dynamic shape
1049 allocation_size *= GetIntImm(x);
1050 }
1051 // allocation feature
1052 fea.alloc_size = allocation_size * node->dtype.bytes();
1053 fea.alloc_prod = allocation_size * outer_loop_prod_;
1054 fea.alloc_outer_prod = outer_loop_prod_;
1055 fea.alloc_inner_prod = fea.outer_prod / outer_loop_prod_;
1056 }
1057
1058 // Extract outer scope related features (group 5)
1059 void ExtractOuterScopeFeature(const Var& buffer) {
1060 FeatureSet& fea = buffer_features[buffer];
1061
1062 fea.outer_prod = outer_loop_prod_;
1063 fea.num_loops = for_loop_stack_.size();
1064 fea.auto_unroll_max_step = cur_auto_unroll_max_step_;
1065 }

1067 // Stores FeatureSet for every buffer
1068 BufferMap<FeatureSet> buffer_features;
1069
1070 private:
1071 // The shared arithmetic analyzer
1072 Analyzer ana_;
1073
1074 // The product of outer loop
1075 float outer_loop_prod_ = 1.0f;
1076
1077 // The stacks to store parent loops during DFS
1078 std::vector<const ForNode*> for_loop_stack_;
1079 std::vector<const ForNode*> parallel_for_stack_;
1080 std::vector<const ForNode*> vec_for_stack_;
1081 std::vector<const ForNode*> unroll_for_stack_;
1082 std::vector<std::vector<std::tuple<Var, PrimExpr>>> variable_definition_stack_;
1083
1084 // GPU-related features
1085 bool is_gpu_{false};
1086 int blockIdx_x_len_{1};
1087 int block_idx_y_len_{1};
1088 int block_idx_z_len_{1};
1089 int threadIdx_x_len_{1};
1090 int thread_idx_y_len_{1};
1091 int thread_idx_z_len_{1};
1092 int vthread_len_{1};
1093 int16_t cur_auto_unroll_max_step_{0};
1094
1095 // Store touch region information for all for loops. The format of this nested map:
1096 // For a loop, for all its touched buffers, for all different accesses to the buffers,
1097 // its (access type, number of touched elements, number of bytes of single element)
1098 std::unordered_map<const ForNode*,
1099 BufferMap<std::vector<std::tuple<BufferAccessType, int64_t, int>>>>
1100 for_touch_regions_;
1101
1102 // The default cache line size in bytes
1103 const int cache_line_size_ = 64;
1104
1105 // Storage of buffer shape and dtype information. Needed because Load/Store
1106 // nodes only do not contain this information.
1107 BufferMap<Array<PrimExpr>> buffer_shapes;
1108 BufferMap<DataType> buffer_dtypes;
1109};

1111// shifted log to incorporate the property that log2p(0) = 0
1112inline float log2p(float x) { return x < 0 ? -std::log2(-x + 1) : std::log2(x + 1); }
1113
1114void GetPerStoreFeature(const PrimFunc& func, int cache_line_size, int max_n_bufs,
1115 std::vector<float>* ret, bool log_scale) {
1116 PerStoreFeatureExtractor extractor(cache_line_size, func->buffer_map);
1117 extractor(func->body);
1118
1119 auto slog = log_scale ? log2p : [](float x) { return x; };
1120
1121 ret->push_back(extractor.buffer_features.size());
1122
1123 for (const auto& x : extractor.buffer_features) {
1124 const FeatureSet& fea_set = x.second;
1125
1126 /***** Group 1: Computation related features *****/
1127 ret->push_back(slog(fea_set.float_mad));
1128 ret->push_back(slog(fea_set.float_addsub));
1129 ret->push_back(slog(fea_set.float_mul));
1130 ret->push_back(slog(fea_set.float_divmod));
1131 ret->push_back(slog(fea_set.float_cmp));
1132 ret->push_back(slog(fea_set.float_math_func));
1133 ret->push_back(slog(fea_set.float_other_func));
1134 ret->push_back(slog(fea_set.int_mad));
1135 ret->push_back(slog(fea_set.int_addsub));
1136 ret->push_back(slog(fea_set.int_mul));
1137 ret->push_back(slog(fea_set.int_divmod));
1138 ret->push_back(slog(fea_set.int_cmp));
1139 ret->push_back(slog(fea_set.int_math_func));
1140 ret->push_back(slog(fea_set.int_other_func));
1141 ret->push_back(slog(fea_set.bool_op));
1142 ret->push_back(slog(fea_set.select_op));
1143
1144 ret->push_back(slog(fea_set.vec_num));
1145 ret->push_back(slog(fea_set.vec_prod));
1146 ret->push_back(slog(fea_set.vec_len));
1147 for (int i = 0; i <= static_cast<int>(AnnotationPosType::kPosMixed); i++) {
1148 ret->push_back(i == static_cast<int>(fea_set.vec_type));
1149 }
1150
1151 ret->push_back(slog(fea_set.unroll_num));
1152 ret->push_back(slog(fea_set.unroll_prod));
1153 ret->push_back(slog(fea_set.unroll_len));
1154 for (int i = 0; i <= static_cast<int>(AnnotationPosType::kPosMixed); i++) {
1155 ret->push_back(i == static_cast<int>(fea_set.unroll_type));
1156 }
1157
1158 ret->push_back(slog(fea_set.parallel_num));
1159 ret->push_back(slog(fea_set.parallel_prod));
1160 ret->push_back(slog(fea_set.parallel_len));
1161 for (int i = 0; i <= static_cast<int>(AnnotationPosType::kPosMixed); i++) {
1162 ret->push_back(i == static_cast<int>(fea_set.parallel_type));
1163 }
1164
1165 ret->push_back(fea_set.is_gpu);
1166 ret->push_back(slog(fea_set.blockIdx_x_len));
1167 ret->push_back(slog(fea_set.blockIdx_y_len));
1168 ret->push_back(slog(fea_set.blockIdx_z_len));
1169 ret->push_back(slog(fea_set.threadIdx_x_len));
1170 ret->push_back(slog(fea_set.threadIdx_y_len));
1171 ret->push_back(slog(fea_set.threadIdx_z_len));
1172 ret->push_back(slog(fea_set.vthread_len));
1173
1174 /***** Group 2: Buffer access related features *****/
1175 // sort according to pair (lines, bytes)
1176 std::vector<std::pair<float, float>> buf_order_key;
1177 for (const auto& acc_fea : fea_set.access_feas) {
1178 buf_order_key.emplace_back(acc_fea.lines, acc_fea.bytes);
1179 }
1180 std::vector<int> buf_order(buf_order_key.size());
1181 std::iota(buf_order.begin(), buf_order.end(), 0);
1182
1183 auto cmp = [&buf_order_key](int l, int r) {
1184 return buf_order_key[l].first > buf_order_key[r].first ||
1185 (buf_order_key[l].first == buf_order_key[r].first &&
1186 buf_order_key[l].second > buf_order_key[r].second);
1187 };
1188 std::sort(buf_order.begin(), buf_order.end(), cmp);
1189 int n_bufs = std::min(max_n_bufs, static_cast<int>(buf_order.size()));
1190 buf_order.resize(n_bufs);
1191
1192 for (int idx : buf_order) {
1193 const auto& acc_fea = fea_set.access_feas[idx];
1194 for (int j = 0; j <= static_cast<int>(BufferAccessType::kReadWrite); ++j) {
1195 ret->push_back(j == static_cast<int>(acc_fea.acc_type));
1196 }
1197 ret->push_back(slog(acc_fea.bytes));
1198 ret->push_back(slog(acc_fea.unique_bytes));
1199 ret->push_back(slog(acc_fea.lines));
1200 ret->push_back(slog(acc_fea.unique_lines));
1201 for (int j = 0; j <= static_cast<int>(ReuseType::kNoReuse); ++j) {
1202 ret->push_back(j == static_cast<int>(acc_fea.reuse_type));
1203 }
1204 ret->push_back(slog(acc_fea.reuse_dis_iter));
1205 ret->push_back(slog(acc_fea.reuse_dis_bytes));
1206 ret->push_back(slog(acc_fea.reuse_ct));
1207 ret->push_back(slog(acc_fea.bytes_d_reuse_ct));
1208 ret->push_back(slog(acc_fea.unique_bytes_d_reuse_ct));
1209 ret->push_back(slog(acc_fea.lines_d_reuse_ct));
1210 ret->push_back(slog(acc_fea.unique_lines_d_reuse_ct));
1211 ret->push_back(slog(acc_fea.stride));
1212 }
1213 // - fill padding
1214 for (int i = 0; i < max_n_bufs - n_bufs; ++i) {
1215 for (int j = 0; j <= static_cast<int>(BufferAccessType::kReadWrite); ++j) { // 3
1216 ret->push_back(0.0f);
1217 }
1218 ret->push_back(0.0f);
1219 ret->push_back(0.0f);
1220 ret->push_back(0.0f);
1221 ret->push_back(0.0f);
1222 for (int j = 0; j <= static_cast<int>(ReuseType::kNoReuse); ++j) { // 3
1223 ret->push_back(0.0f);
1224 }
1225 ret->push_back(0.0f);
1226 ret->push_back(0.0f);
1227 ret->push_back(0.0f);
1228 ret->push_back(0.0f);
1229 ret->push_back(0.0f);
1230 ret->push_back(0.0f);
1231 ret->push_back(0.0f);
1232 ret->push_back(0.0f);
1233 }
1234
1235 /***** Group 3: Arithmetic intensity related features *****/
1236 for (size_t i = 0; i < ARITH_INTENSITY_CURVE_SAMPLE_N; ++i) {
1237 ret->push_back(slog(fea_set.arith_intensity_curve[i]));
1238 }
1239
1240 /***** Group 4: Allocation related features *****/
1241 ret->push_back(slog(fea_set.alloc_size));
1242 ret->push_back(slog(fea_set.alloc_prod));
1243 ret->push_back(slog(fea_set.alloc_outer_prod));
1244 ret->push_back(slog(fea_set.alloc_inner_prod));
1245
1246 /***** Group 5: Outer scope related features *****/
1247 ret->push_back(slog(fea_set.outer_prod));
1248 ret->push_back(slog(fea_set.num_loops));
1249 ret->push_back(slog(fea_set.auto_unroll_max_step));
1250 }
1251}

1358void GetPerStoreFeaturesWorkerFunc(const SearchTask& task, const State& state, int max_n_bufs,
1359 std::vector<float>* feature, std::atomic<int>* error_ct) {
1360 auto [sch, tensors] = task->compute_dag.ApplySteps(state->transform_steps);
1361
1362 // When inlining, replace const matrices with const values.
1363 // Produces wrong IR, but good enough for feature extraction, and
1364 // can improve the speed of feature extraction/search. Must be
1365 // called before ScheduleToModule to have an effect.
1366 sch = sch.normalize_for_feature_extraction();
1367
1368 try {
1369 const std::string& name = "main";
1370 auto pass_ctx = tvm::transform::PassContext::Current();
1371
1372 auto mod = ScheduleToModule(sch, Array<ObjectRef>{tensors.begin(), tensors.end()}, name,
1373 std::unordered_map<te::Tensor, te::Buffer>(),
1374 GlobalVarSupply(NameSupply("")));
1375
1376 bool disable_vectorize =
1377 pass_ctx->GetConfig<Bool>("tir.disable_vectorize", Bool(false)).value();
1378 bool instrument_bound_checkers =
1379 pass_ctx->GetConfig<Bool>("tir.instrument_bound_checkers", Bool(false)).value();
1380
1381 if (IsGPUTask(task)) {
1382 auto pass_list = Array<tvm::transform::Pass>();
1383 // Phase 0
1384 pass_list.push_back(tir::transform::InjectPrefetch());
1385 pass_list.push_back(tir::transform::StorageFlatten(64, instrument_bound_checkers));
1386 // Phase 1
1387 pass_list.push_back(tir::transform::NarrowDataType(32));
1388 pass_list.push_back(tir::transform::Simplify());
1389 pass_list.push_back(tir::transform::VectorizeLoop(!disable_vectorize));
1390 pass_list.push_back(tir::transform::InjectVirtualThread());
1391 pass_list.push_back(tir::transform::StorageRewrite());
1392 pass_list.push_back(tir::transform::Simplify());
1393 tvm::Map<String, tvm::PrimExpr> gpu_params{
1394 {"max_shared_memory_per_block", task->hardware_params->max_shared_memory_per_block},
1395 {"max_local_memory_per_block", task->hardware_params->max_local_memory_per_block},
1396 {"max_threads_per_block", task->hardware_params->max_threads_per_block},
1397 {"max_vector_bytes", task->hardware_params->vector_unit_bytes},
1398 {"max_vthread", task->hardware_params->max_vthread_extent},
1399 };
1400 pass_list.push_back(tir::transform::VerifyGPUCode(gpu_params));
1401 const auto& optimize = tir::transform::Sequential(pass_list);
1402 optimize(mod);
1403 }
1404 const auto& optimize =
1405 tir::transform::Sequential(Array<tvm::transform::Pass>{tir::transform::Simplify()});
1406 mod = optimize(std::move(mod));
1407 PrimFunc prim_func = Downcast<PrimFunc>(mod->Lookup(name));
1408 GetPerStoreFeature(prim_func, task->hardware_params->cache_line_bytes, max_n_bufs, feature);
1409 } catch (Error& e) {
1410 (*error_ct)++;
1411 }
1412}

1414void GetPerStoreFeaturesFromStates(const Array<State>& states, const SearchTask& task,
1415 int skip_first_n_feature_extraction, int max_n_bufs,
1416 std::vector<std::vector<float>>* features) {
1417 // extract features
1418 features->assign(states.size(), std::vector<float>());
1419
1420 std::atomic<int> error_ct(0);
1421
1422 support::parallel_for(skip_first_n_feature_extraction, states.size(),
1423 [&task, &states, &max_n_bufs, &features, &error_ct](int i) {
1424 GetPerStoreFeaturesWorkerFunc(task, states[i], max_n_bufs,
1425 &(*features)[i], &error_ct);
1426 });
1427}

1429void GetPerStoreFeaturesFromStates(const Array<State>& states, const std::vector<SearchTask>& tasks,
1430 int skip_first_n_feature_extraction, int max_n_bufs,
1431 std::vector<std::vector<float>>* features) {

1437 support::parallel_for(skip_first_n_feature_extraction, states.size(),
1438 [&tasks, &states, &max_n_bufs, &features, &error_ct](int i) {

1441 });

1444void GetPerStoreFeaturesFromFile(const std::string& filename, int max_lines, int max_n_bufs,
1445 std::vector<std::vector<float>>* features,
1446 std::vector<float>* normalized_throughputs,
1447 std::vector<int>* task_ids) {
1448 Array<State> states;
1449 std::vector<SearchTask> tasks;
1450
1451 normalized_throughputs->clear();
1452 task_ids->clear();
1453
1454 // (workload_key, target) -> (search_task, task_id)
1455 std::unordered_map<std::pair<std::string, std::string>, std::pair<SearchTask, size_t>> task_cache;
1456 // task_id -> min_cost
1457 std::vector<float> min_costs;
1458
1459 const auto* workload_key_to_tensors =
1460 tvm::runtime::Registry::Get("auto_scheduler.workload_key_to_tensors");
1461 ICHECK(workload_key_to_tensors != nullptr);
1462
1463 // read from file
1464 RecordReader reader(filename);
1465 auto cur_inp = make_object<MeasureInputNode>();
1466 auto cur_res = make_object<MeasureResultNode>();
1467 while (reader->ReadNext(cur_inp.get(), cur_res.get())) {
1468 float cost = static_cast<float>(FloatArrayMean(cur_res->costs));
1469 const std::string& workload_key = cur_inp->task->workload_key;
1470
1471 SearchTask task;
1472 size_t task_id;
1473 std::pair<std::string, std::string> key(workload_key, cur_inp->task->target->str());
1474 auto find_res = task_cache.find(key);
1475 if (find_res == task_cache.end()) {
1476 // rebuild task
1477 Array<te::Tensor> tensors = (*workload_key_to_tensors)(workload_key);
1478 Target target = cur_inp->task->target;
1479 Target target_host = cur_inp->task->target_host;
1480 CheckAndUpdateHostConsistency(&target, &target_host);
1481 task = SearchTask(ComputeDAG(tensors), workload_key, target, target_host,
1482 cur_inp->task->hardware_params, cur_inp->task->layout_rewrite_option,
1483 cur_inp->task->task_input_names);
1484 task_id = task_cache.size();
1485
1486 // compute min cost for each task
1487 task_cache.insert(std::make_pair(key, std::make_pair(task, task_id)));
1488 min_costs.push_back(cost);
1489 } else {
1490 std::tie(task, task_id) = find_res->second;
1491 min_costs[task_id] = std::min(min_costs[task_id], cost);
1492 }
1493
1494 tasks.push_back(std::move(task));
1495 task_ids->push_back(task_id);
1496 states.push_back(cur_inp->state);
1497 normalized_throughputs->push_back(cost);
1498
1499 if (max_lines > 0 && static_cast<int>(states.size()) >= max_lines) {
1500 break;
1501 }
1502 }
1503
1504 for (size_t i = 0; i < normalized_throughputs->size(); ++i) {
1505 (*normalized_throughputs)[i] = min_costs[(*task_ids)[i]] / (*normalized_throughputs)[i];
1506 }
1507
1508 GetPerStoreFeaturesFromStates(states, tasks, 0, max_n_bufs, features);
1509}

1511void GetPerStoreFeaturesFromMeasurePairs(const Array<MeasureInput>& inputs,
1512 const Array<MeasureResult>& results,
1513 int skip_first_n_feature_extraction, int max_n_bufs,
1514 std::vector<std::vector<float>>* features,
1515 std::vector<float>* normalized_throughputs,
1516 std::vector<int>* task_ids) {
1517 Array<State> states;
1518 std::vector<SearchTask> tasks;
1519
1520 normalized_throughputs->clear();
1521 task_ids->clear();
1522
1523 // (workload_key, target) -> (search_task, task_id)
1524 std::unordered_map<std::pair<std::string, std::string>, std::pair<SearchTask, size_t>> task_cache;
1525 // task_id -> min_cost
1526 std::vector<float> min_costs;
1527
1528 const auto* workload_key_to_tensors =
1529 tvm::runtime::Registry::Get("auto_scheduler.workload_key_to_tensors");
1530 ICHECK(workload_key_to_tensors != nullptr);
1531
1532 tasks.reserve(inputs.size());
1533 normalized_throughputs->reserve(inputs.size());
1534 task_ids->reserve(inputs.size());
1535 for (size_t i = 0; i < inputs.size(); ++i) {
1536 float cost = static_cast<float>(FloatArrayMean(results[i]->costs));
1537 const std::string& workload_key = inputs[i]->task->workload_key;
1538 SearchTask task;
1539
1540 size_t task_id;
1541 std::pair<std::string, std::string> key(workload_key, inputs[i]->task->target->str());
1542 auto find_res = task_cache.find(key);
1543 if (find_res == task_cache.end()) {
1544 if (inputs[i]->task->compute_dag.defined()) { // the measure input is complete
1545 task = inputs[i]->task;
1546 } else {
1547 // The measure input is incomplete, rebuild task for incomplete measure pairs read from file
1548 try {
1549 Array<te::Tensor> tensors = (*workload_key_to_tensors)(workload_key);
1550 Target target = inputs[i]->task->target;
1551 Target target_host = inputs[i]->task->target_host;
1552 CheckAndUpdateHostConsistency(&target, &target_host);
1553 task =
1554 SearchTask(ComputeDAG(tensors), workload_key, target, target_host,
1555 inputs[i]->task->hardware_params, inputs[i]->task->layout_rewrite_option,
1556 inputs[i]->task->task_input_names);
1557 } catch (std::exception& e) {
1558 // Cannot build ComputeDAG from workload key, the task may have not been registered in
1559 // this search round
1560 continue;
1561 }
1562 }
1563 task_id = task_cache.size();
1564
1565 // compute min cost for each task
1566 task_cache.insert(std::make_pair(key, std::make_pair(task, task_id)));
1567 min_costs.push_back(cost);
1568 } else {
1569 std::tie(task, task_id) = find_res->second;
1570 min_costs[task_id] = std::min(min_costs[task_id], cost);
1571 }
1572
1573 tasks.push_back(std::move(task));
1574 task_ids->push_back(task_id);
1575 states.push_back(inputs[i]->state);
1576 normalized_throughputs->push_back(cost);
1577 }
1578
1579 for (size_t i = 0; i < normalized_throughputs->size(); ++i) {
1580 (*normalized_throughputs)[i] = min_costs[(*task_ids)[i]] / (*normalized_throughputs)[i];
1581 }
1582
1583 GetPerStoreFeaturesFromStates(states, tasks, skip_first_n_feature_extraction, max_n_bufs,
1584 features);
1585}

1587/*
1588 * \brief Serialize a two-dimensional variable-size feature vector with normalized throughputs
1589 * and task ids to a one-dimensional flatten byte array.
1590 *
1591 * For faster data copy between c++ and python, the c++ part returns features in a single
1592 * flatten array using a packed format. The python part then unpacks the flatten array.
1593 *
1594 * The packed format for n records is:
1595 * {
1596 * int n;
1597 * int sizes[n+2]; // The sizes for the following arrays
1598 *
1599 * float features_0[size[0]]; // The features for record 0
1600 * float features_1[size[1]]; // The features for record 1
1601 * ...
1602 * float features_i[size[i]]; // The features for record i
1603 * ... // until i == n - 1
1604 *
1605 * float throughputs[sizes[n]]; // The normalized throughputs for n records
1606 * int task_ids[size[n+1]]; // The task ids for n records
1607 *
1608 * }
1609 * To implement this format, we also store int as float, so we can store all numbers
1610 * into a single float array.
1611 */
1612TVMByteArray SerializeFeatures(std::vector<std::vector<float>>&& features,
1613 std::vector<float>&& normalized_throughputs,
1614 std::vector<int>&& task_ids, std::vector<char>* out_data) {
1615 size_t total_bytes = 0;
1616 std::vector<int> size_vector;
1617
1618 int n = features.size();
1619
1620 // serialize sizes
1621 size_t size_vector_size = 1 + n + 2;
1622 total_bytes += size_vector_size * sizeof(int);
1623
1624 size_vector.reserve(size_vector_size);
1625 size_vector.push_back(features.size());
1626 for (const auto& x : features) {
1627 size_vector.push_back(static_cast<int>(x.size()));
1628 total_bytes += sizeof(float) * x.size();
1629 }
1630 size_vector.push_back(static_cast<int>(normalized_throughputs.size()));
1631 total_bytes += sizeof(float) * normalized_throughputs.size();
1632 size_vector.push_back(static_cast<int>(task_ids.size()));
1633 total_bytes += sizeof(int) * task_ids.size();
1634
1635 ICHECK_EQ(size_vector.size(), size_vector_size);
1636
1637 // allocate memory
1638 out_data->reserve(total_bytes);
1639 char* ptr = out_data->data();
1640
1641 // serialize size_vector
1642 memmove(ptr, reinterpret_cast<char*>(size_vector.data()), size_vector.size() * sizeof(int));
1643 ptr += size_vector.size() * sizeof(int);
1644
1645 // serialize features
1646 for (auto& x : features) {
1647 memmove(ptr, x.data(), sizeof(float) * x.size());
1648 ptr += sizeof(float) * x.size();
1649 x.clear();
1650 }
1651
1652 // serialize normalized_throughputs
1653 memmove(ptr, reinterpret_cast<char*>(normalized_throughputs.data()),
1654 normalized_throughputs.size() * sizeof(int));
1655 ptr += normalized_throughputs.size() * sizeof(int);
1656
1657 // serialize task_ids
1658 memmove(ptr, reinterpret_cast<char*>(task_ids.data()), task_ids.size() * sizeof(int));
1659 ptr += task_ids.size() * sizeof(int);
1660
1661 ICHECK_EQ(ptr - out_data->data(), total_bytes);
1662
1663 return TVMByteArray{out_data->data(), total_bytes};
1664}
1665
1666TVM_REGISTER_GLOBAL("auto_scheduler.GetPerStoreFeaturesFromFile")
1667 .set_body([](TVMArgs args, TVMRetValue* ret) {
1668 std::string filename = args[0];
1669 int max_lines = args[1];
1670 int max_n_bufs = args[2];
1671
1672 std::vector<std::vector<float>> features;
1673 std::vector<float> normalized_throughputs;

1735TVM_REGISTER_GLOBAL("auto_scheduler.FeaturesFromPrimFunc")
1736 .set_body_typed([](const PrimFunc& func, int cache_line_size, int max_n_bufs, bool log_scale) {
1737 std::vector<float> vec;
1738 GetPerStoreFeature(func, cache_line_size, max_n_bufs, &vec, log_scale);
1739 int64_t num_feature_rows = vec[0]; // first element is number of rows
1740 int64_t row_length = (vec.size() - 1) / num_feature_rows;
1741 auto ary =
1742 runtime::NDArray::Empty({num_feature_rows, row_length}, {kDLFloat, 32, 1}, {kDLCPU, 0});
1743 // NDArray is row major by default
1744 ary.CopyFromBytes(vec.data() + 1, sizeof(float) * num_feature_rows * row_length);
1745 return ary;
1746 });
